# Awesome Portfolio Template

Next.js 16 + Tailwind CSS v4 + Framer Motion + next-intl (i18n) + next-themes (dark mode).

Users customize by editing `src/config/site.ts` and `src/data/` files. Do NOT modify component code for basic personalization.

## Key Files

| Purpose | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Central config | `src/config/site.ts` (URL, author, social, nav, sections, SEO) |
| Content data | `src/data/*.ts` (profile, experience, career, credentials, speaking, projects) |
| i18n strings | `src/messages/ko.json`, `src/messages/en.json` |
| Profile image | `public/profile.png` |
| Global styles | `src/app/globals.css` |
| Main page | `src/app/[locale]/page.tsx` |

## Conventions

- **Tailwind v4**: `@import "tailwindcss"`, NO `@apply`, utility classes in JSX, `cn()` for merging
- **Framer Motion**: ALWAYS `m`, NEVER `motion` (LazyMotion provider active)
- **i18n**: All text via `useTranslations()` or data file `ko`/`en` fields. Default locale: `ko`
- **Dark mode**: `dark:` variants, system preference + manual toggle via next-themes
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode, `NavKey` type from `siteConfig.nav`

## Anti-Patterns

- NEVER use `motion` (use `m`)
- NEVER hardcode URLs/author info (use `siteConfig`)
- NEVER use `@apply`
- NEVER `as any` / `@ts-ignore`
- NEVER skip i18n for user-facing text
- NEVER put content in components (use `src/data/`)
- NEVER use `transition-all` (be specific)

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # localhost:3000
npm run build    # Production build
npm run lint     # ESLint
```
